scription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field Image"},{"range":{"start":{"line":649,"character":7},"end":{"line":649,"character":7}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field Image"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register_test.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info_test.go":[]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md\n@@ -95,7 +95,55 @@\n - **WHEN** `go build ./pkg/apis/...` is executed\n - **THEN** the command SHALL exit with code 0 and produce no errors\n \n #### Scenario: Unit tests pass\n-- **GIVEN** the test file `shared_types_test.go` exists\n+- **GIVEN** the test files `codeinterpreter_types_test.go`, `agent_type_test.go`, `register_test.go`, and `groupversion_info_test.go` exist\n - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` is executed\n-- **THEN** all tests SHALL pass, including `ProtocolType` constant tests, `AuthModeType` constant tests, and `TargetPort` zero-value/full-field tests\n+- **THEN** all tests SHALL pass, including `ProtocolType` constant tests, `AuthModeType` constant tests, `TargetPort` zero-value/full-field tests, scheme registration tests, and GroupVersion constant tests\n+\n+### Requirement: GroupVersion and SchemeBuilder\n+\n+The system SHALL define `GroupVersion` as `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`, a `SchemeBuilder` using `scheme.Builder`, and `AddToScheme` as the builder's add function.\n+\n+#### Scenario: GroupVersion has correct group and version\n+- **GIVEN** the `GroupVersion` constant in `groupversion_info.go`\n+- **WHEN** its fields are inspected\n+- **THEN** `GroupVersion.Group` SHALL equal `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` and `GroupVersion.Version` SHALL equal `\"v1alpha1\"`\n+\n+#### Scenario: SchemeBuilder is configured with GroupVersion\n+- **GIVEN** the `SchemeBuilder` variable\n+- **WHEN** its GroupVersion is inspected\n+- **THEN** it SHALL equal `GroupVersion`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AddToScheme delegates to SchemeBuilder\n+- **GIVEN** the `AddToScheme` variable\n+- **WHEN** it is compared to `SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme`\n+- **THEN** they SHALL be the same function\n+\n+### Requirement: Kind and GroupVersionKind constants\n+\n+The system SHALL define kind constants (`CodeInterpreterKind`, `CodeInterpreterListKind`, `AgentRuntimeKind`, `AgentRuntimeListKind`) and GroupVersionKind constants (`CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind`, `CodeInterpreterGroupKind`, `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind`) in `register.go`.\n+\n+#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter kind constants are correct\n+- **GIVEN** the constants in `register.go`\n+- **WHEN** they are inspected\n+- **THEN** `CodeInterpreterKind` SHALL equal `\"CodeInterpreter\"`, `CodeInterpreterListKind` SHALL equal `\"CodeInterpreterList\"`, and `CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind` SHALL equal `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AgentRuntime kind constants are correct\n+- **GIVEN** the constants in `register.go`\n+- **WHEN** they are inspected\n+- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeKind` SHALL equal `\"AgentRuntime\"`, `AgentRuntimeListKind` SHALL equal `\"AgentRuntimeList\"`, and `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind` SHALL equal `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")`\n+\n+#### Scenario: SchemeGroupVersion aliases GroupVersion\n+- **GIVEN** the `SchemeGroupVersion` variable in `register.go`\n+- **WHEN** it is compared to `GroupVersion`\n+- **THEN** they SHALL be equal\n+\n+#### Scenario: Resource helper returns correct GroupVersionResource\n+- **GIVEN** the `Resource(resource string)` helper function\n+- **WHEN** called with `\"agentruntimes\"`\n+- **THEN** it SHALL return `schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}`\n+\n+#### Scenario: Resource helper works for codeinterpreters\n+- **GIVEN** the `Resource(resource string)` helper function\n+- **WHEN** called with `\"codeinterpreters\"`\n+- **THEN** it SHALL return `schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}`\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md","before":"# AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量 — Delta Spec\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine shared types and constants in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` that are reused across AgentRuntime (AR-001) and CodeInterpreter (AR-002) CRD type definitions, establishing a single source of truth for port configuration, protocol enumeration, and authentication mode types.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ProtocolType enumeration\n\nThe system SHALL define `ProtocolType` as a typed string constant with values `HTTP` and `HTTPS`, serving as the protocol enumeration for sandbox port configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: ProtocolType constants have correct values\n- **GIVEN** the constants `ProtocolTypeHTTP` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` are defined\n- **WHEN** their values are inspected\n- **THEN** `ProtocolTypeHTTP` SHALL equal `\"HTTP\"` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` SHALL equal `\"HTTPS\"`\n\n#### Scenario: ProtocolType underlying type is string\n- **GIVEN** the `ProtocolType` type definition\n- **WHEN** the underlying type is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `string`, enabling JSON serialization without custom marshalers\n\n### Requirement: AuthModeType enumeration\n\nThe system SHALL define `AuthModeType` as a typed string constant with values `picod` and `none`, serving as the authentication mode enumeration for sandbox configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: AuthModeType constants have correct values\n- **GIVEN** the constants `AuthModePicoD` and `AuthModeNone` are defined\n- **WHEN** their values are inspected\n- **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` SHALL equal `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` SHALL equal `\"none\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AuthModeType underlying type is string\n- **GIVEN** the `AuthModeType` type definition\n- **WHEN** the underlying type is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `string`, enabling JSON serialization without custom marshalers\n\n### Requirement: TargetPort struct\n\nThe system SHALL define `TargetPort` as a struct with fields for URL path prefix (`PathPrefix`), port name (`Name`), port number (`Port`), and protocol (`Protocol`), with appropriate JSON tags for Kubernetes CRD serialization.\n\n#### Scenario: TargetPort serializes with correct JSON keys\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` instance with all fields populated\n- **WHEN** the struct is serialized to JSON\n- **THEN** the output SHALL use camelCase keys: `pathPrefix`, `name`, `port`, `protocol`\n\n#### Scenario: TargetPort omits empty optional fields\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with only `Port` set to `8080`\n- **WHEN** the struct is serialized to JSON\n- **THEN** `pathPrefix`, `name`, and `protocol` SHALL be omitted from the output (omitempty behavior)\n\n#### Scenario: TargetPort Port field is required\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` struct definition\n- **WHEN** the JSON tags are inspected\n- **THEN** `Port` SHALL NOT have `omitempty`, making it a required field in CRD validation\n\n### Requirement: Single source of truth\n\nThe system SHALL define `ProtocolType`, `AuthModeType`, and `TargetPort` exactly once in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`, with both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types referencing these shared definitions rather than duplicating them.\n\n#### Scenario: No duplicate type definitions\n- **GIVEN** the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` package\n- **WHEN** the package is compiled\n- **THEN** there SHALL be exactly one definition each of `ProtocolType`, `AuthModeType`, and `TargetPort`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime references shared types\n- **GIVEN** the `agent_type.go` file\n- **WHEN** the type definitions are inspected\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeSpec` SHALL reference the shared `TargetPort` type for its port configuration\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter references shared types\n- **GIVEN** the `codeinterpreter_types.go` file\n- **WHEN** the type definitions are inspected\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL reference the shared `TargetPort` type for its `Ports` field\n\n### Requirement: DeepCopy generation for TargetPort\n\nThe system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` and `DeepCopyInto` methods for `TargetPort` via `controller-gen object`, ensuring safe cross-goroutine value copying.\n\n#### Scenario: DeepCopy methods exist for TargetPort\n- **GIVEN** `make generate` has been run\n- **WHEN** `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `DeepCopyInto` and `DeepCopy` methods for `TargetPort`\n\n#### Scenario: DeepCopy produces independent copies\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Name` set to `\"web\"`\n- **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called and the copy's `Name` is modified\n- **THEN** the original's `Name` SHALL remain `\"web\"` (no shared references)\n\n### Requirement: Build and test integrity\n\nThe system SHALL compile cleanly and pass all unit tests for the shared types.\n\n#### Scenario: Package compiles\n- **GIVEN** Go toolchain and all dependencies are available\n- **WHEN** `go build ./pkg/apis/...` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL exit with code 0 and produce no errors\n\n#### Scenario: Unit tests pass\n- **GIVEN** the test file `shared_types_test.go` exists\n- **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` is executed\n- **THEN** all tests SHALL pass, including `ProtocolType` constant tests, `AuthModeType` constant tests, and `TargetPort` zero-value/full-field tests\n","after":"# AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量 — Delta Spec\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine shared types and constants in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` that are reused across AgentRuntime (AR-001) and CodeInterpreter (AR-002) CRD type definitions, establishing a single source of truth for port configuration, protocol enumeration, and authentication mode types.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ProtocolType enumeration\n\nThe system SHALL define `ProtocolType` as a typed string constant with values `HTTP` and `HTTPS`, serving as the protocol enumeration for sandbox port configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: ProtocolType constants have correct values\n- **GIVEN** the constants `ProtocolTypeHTTP` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` are defined\n- **WHEN** their values are inspected\n- **THEN** `ProtocolTypeHTTP` SHALL equal `\"HTTP\"` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` SHALL equal `\"HTTPS\"`\n\n#### Scenario: ProtocolType underlying type is string\n- **GIVEN** the `ProtocolType` type definition\n- **WHEN** the underlying type is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `string`, enabling JSON serialization without custom marshalers\n\n### Requirement: AuthModeType enumeration\n\nThe system SHALL define `AuthModeType` as a typed string constant with values `picod` and `none`, serving as the authentication mode enumeration for sandbox configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: AuthModeType constants have correct values\n- **GIVEN** the constants `AuthModePicoD` and `AuthModeNone` are defined\n- **WHEN** their values are inspected\n- **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` SHALL equal `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` SHALL equal `\"none\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AuthModeType underlying type is string\n- **GIVEN** the `AuthModeType` type definition\n- **WHEN** the underlying type is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `string`, enabling JSON serialization without custom marshalers\n\n### Requirement: TargetPort struct\n\nThe system SHALL define `TargetPort` as a struct with fields for URL path prefix (`PathPrefix`), port name (`Name`), port number (`Port`), and protocol (`Protocol`), with appropriate JSON tags for Kubernetes CRD serialization.\n\n#### Scenario: TargetPort serializes with correct JSON keys\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` instance with all fields populated\n- **WHEN** the struct is serialized to JSON\n- **THEN** the output SHALL use camelCase keys: `pathPrefix`, `name`, `port`, `protocol`\n\n#### Scenario: TargetPort omits empty optional fields\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with only `Port` set to `8080`\n- **WHEN** the struct is serialized to JSON\n- **THEN** `pathPrefix`, `name`, and `protocol` SHALL be omitted from the output (omitempty behavior)\n\n#### Scenario: TargetPort Port field is required\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` struct definition\n- **WHEN** the JSON tags are inspected\n- **THEN** `Port` SHALL NOT have `omitempty`, making it a required field in CRD validation\n\n### Requirement: Single source of truth\n\nThe system SHALL define `ProtocolType`, `AuthModeType`, and `TargetPort` exactly once in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`, with both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types referencing these shared definitions rather than duplicating them.\n\n#### Scenario: No duplicate type definitions\n- **GIVEN** the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` package\n- **WHEN** the package is compiled\n- **THEN** there SHALL be exactly one definition each of `ProtocolType`, `AuthModeType`, and `TargetPort`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime references shared types\n- **GIVEN** the `agent_type.go` file\n- **WHEN** the type definitions are inspected\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeSpec` SHALL reference the shared `TargetPort` type for its port configuration\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter references shared types\n- **GIVEN** the `codeinterpreter_types.go` file\n- **WHEN** the type definitions are inspected\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL reference the shared `TargetPort` type for its `Ports` field\n\n### Requirement: DeepCopy generation for TargetPort\n\nThe system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` and `DeepCopyInto` methods for `TargetPort` via `controller-gen object`, ensuring safe cross-goroutine value copying.\n\n#### Scenario: DeepCopy methods exist for TargetPort\n- **GIVEN** `make generate` has been run\n- **WHEN** `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `DeepCopyInto` and `DeepCopy` methods for `TargetPort`\n\n#### Scenario: DeepCopy produces independent copies\n- **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Name` set to `\"web\"`\n- **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called and the copy's `Name` is modified\n- **THEN** the original's `Name` SHALL remain `\"web\"` (no shared references)\n\n### Requirement: Build and test integrity\n\nThe system SHALL compile cleanly and pass all unit tests for the shared types.\n\n#### Scenario: Package compiles\n- **GIVEN** Go toolchain and all dependencies are available\n- **WHEN** `go build ./pkg/apis/...` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL exit with code 0 and produce no errors\n\n#### Scenario: Unit tests pass\n- **GIVEN** the test files `codeinterpreter_types_test.go`, `agent_type_test.go`, `register_test.go`, and `groupversion_info_test.go` exist\n- **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` is executed\n- **THEN** all tests SHALL pass, including `ProtocolType` constant tests, `AuthModeType` constant tests, `TargetPort` zero-value/full-field tests, scheme registration tests, and GroupVersion constant tests\n\n### Requirement: GroupVersion and SchemeBuilder\n\nThe system SHALL define `GroupVersion` as `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`, a `SchemeBuilder` using `scheme.Builder`, and `AddToScheme` as the builder's add function.\n\n#### Scenario: GroupVersion has correct group and version\n- **GIVEN** the `GroupVersion` constant in `groupversion_info.go`\n- **WHEN** its fields are inspected\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion.Group` SHALL equal `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` and `GroupVersion.Version` SHALL equal `\"v1alpha1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: SchemeBuilder is configured with GroupVersion\n- **GIVEN** the `SchemeBuilder` variable\n- **WHEN** its GroupVersion is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `GroupVersion`\n\n#### Scenario: AddToScheme delegates to SchemeBuilder\n- **GIVEN** the `AddToScheme` variable\n- **WHEN** it is compared to `SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme`\n- **THEN** they SHALL be the same function\n\n### Requirement: Kind and GroupVersionKind constants\n\nThe system SHALL define kind constants (`CodeInterpreterKind`, `CodeInterpreterListKind`, `AgentRuntimeKind`, `AgentRuntimeListKind`) and GroupVersionKind constants (`CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind`, `CodeInterpreterGroupKind`, `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind`) in `register.go`.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter kind constants are correct\n- **GIVEN** the constants in `register.go`\n- **WHEN** they are inspected\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreterKind` SHALL equal `\"CodeInterpreter\"`, `CodeInterpreterListKind` SHALL equal `\"CodeInterpreterList\"`, and `CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind` SHALL equal `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime kind constants are correct\n- **GIVEN** the constants in `register.go`\n- **WHEN** they are inspected\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeKind` SHALL equal `\"AgentRuntime\"`, `AgentRuntimeListKind` SHALL equal `\"AgentRuntimeList\"`, and `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind` SHALL equal `GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")`\n\n#### Scenario: SchemeGroupVersion aliases GroupVersion\n- **GIVEN** the `SchemeGroupVersion` variable in `register.go`\n- **WHEN** it is compared to `GroupVersion`\n- **THEN** they SHALL be equal\n\n#### Scenario: Resource helper returns correct GroupVersionResource\n- **GIVEN** the `Resource(resource string)` helper function\n- **WHEN** called with `\"agentruntimes\"`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource helper works for codeinterpreters\n- **GIVEN** the `Resource(resource string)` helper function\n- **WHEN** called with `\"codeinterpreters\"`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}`\n","additions":50,"deletions":2},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775811241095,"end":1775811241117}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775811241221,"sessionID":"ses_28967f6c4ffeTb2nhfnQe2La7G","part":{"id":"prt_d7698dc7b001UGpLyZQsZQ3O7Q","messageID":"msg_d76988539001BN5vogjxEukmLG","sessionID":"ses_28967f6c4ffeTb2nhfnQe2La7G","type":"text","text":"The delta-spec.md already exists at `changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md`. After reviewing it against the actual codebase, I notice a few discrepancies that should be corrected:\n\n1. **Test file reference**: Spec references `shared_types_test.go` but actual tests are in `codeinterpreter_types_test.go` and `agent_type_test.go`\n2. **Missing coverage**: `register.go` constants (`CodeInterpreterKind`, `AgentRuntimeKind`, etc.) and `SchemeGroupVersion` alias are not covered\n3. **Missing coverage**: `groupversion_info.go` (`GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`) is not covered","time":{"start":1775811241219,"end":1775811241219}}}
